This paper deals with the problem of predicting the performance of software configurations using machine learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SE (Software Engineering). The paper also discusses various supervised machine learning techniques and sampling strategies, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) research. Additionally, the paper focuses on the optimization of non-functional properties, which is related to programming languages (cs.PL) and system design (cs.SY).
